.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH webp 1  "webp 0.1.0" 
.SH NAME
webp \- Command\-line tools for the webpkit WebP codec: libwebp\-style cwebp (lossy by default, \-lossless for VP8L) / dwebp and the webp brand tool.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBwebp\fR [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]... [\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-\-color\fR] [\fB\-\-threads\fR] [\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quality\fR] [\fB\-\-lossless\fR] [\fB\-\-lossy\fR] [\fB\-m\fR|\fB\-\-method\fR] [\fB\-\-metadata\fR] [\fB\-\-crop\fR] [\fB\-\-resize\fR] [\fB\-r\fR|\fB\-\-recursive\fR] [\fB\-\-force\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-clobber\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fIINPUTS\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Command\-line tools for the webpkit WebP codec: libwebp\-style cwebp (lossy by default, \-lossless for VP8L) / dwebp and the webp brand tool.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Print per\-stage detail on stderr
.TP
\fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress all non\-error output.

Long\-only: `\-q` is `\-\-quality`. A bare `webp \-q photo.png` therefore reads `photo.png` as a quality value and fails; use `\-\-quiet` to silence output.
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR \fI<WHEN>\fR [default: auto]
auto, always, or never

`CLICOLOR_FORCE` and `NO_COLOR` are honored, and an explicit `\-\-color` outranks both. Left alone, messages are colored only when stderr is a terminal — so a pipe or a log file never receives escape codes.
.TP
\fB\-\-threads\fR \fI<N>\fR
Worker threads for parallel work; 0 (the default) uses one per core.

One global thread pool is built, which the encoder\*(Aqs parallel `best` search draws from too — so this single number bounds every layer of parallelism, batch conversion and per\-image search alike.
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR
Output file, or a directory for many inputs; default: beside each input
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quality\fR \fI<QUALITY>\fR
Lossy quality 0\-100 (higher = larger, closer to source); selects lossy
.TP
\fB\-\-lossless\fR
Force lossless (VP8L) encoding
.TP
\fB\-\-lossy\fR
Force lossy (VP8) encoding
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-method\fR \fI<METHOD>\fR [default: balanced]
Encoder effort
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
fast: Fastest: literal + subtract\-green only
.IP \(bu 2
balanced: Balanced (the default): LZ77 + color cache
.IP \(bu 2
best: Smallest: adds Tier 3 forward transforms and meta\-Huffman on top of Balanced
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-metadata\fR \fI<METADATA>\fR
Metadata to embed: all,none,icc,exif,xmp (default: all)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
all: Keep ICC, Exif, and XMP
.IP \(bu 2
none: Strip everything (a bare `VP8L` output)
.IP \(bu 2
icc: Keep the ICC color profile
.IP \(bu 2
exif: Keep Exif
.IP \(bu 2
xmp: Keep XMP
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-crop\fR \fI<X,Y,W,H>\fR
Crop before encoding: `x,y,width,height` in pixels (applied before \-\-resize)
.TP
\fB\-\-resize\fR \fI<WxH>\fR
Resize before encoding: `WxH` (use 0 on one axis to keep aspect)
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-recursive\fR
Recurse into subdirectories
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
Overwrite an existing derived output
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-clobber\fR
Skip an existing derived output instead of failing (still exits 0)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.TP
[\fIINPUTS\fR]
Images or directories. A WebP is decoded to PNG; anything else is encoded
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
webp\-decode(1)
Decode a WebP file to PNG (default), PPM/PAM, or raw pixels
.TP
webp\-encode(1)
Encode an image (PNG/JPEG/GIF/TIFF/BMP/PPM/PAM/raw) into a WebP file
.TP
webp\-convert(1)
Batch\-convert many images (or directories) to WebP, in parallel
.TP
webp\-info(1)
Print a summary of a WebP file (size, alpha, metadata, animation)
.TP
webp\-diff(1)
Compare two images: report PSNR and the largest per\-channel difference
.TP
webp\-doctor(1)
Diagnose the environment: PATH drop\-in shadows, config, terminal, threads
.TP
webp\-config(1)
Show resolved settings and where each came from (args, env, file, default)
.TP
webp\-explain(1)
Explain an exit code: what a failing run\*(Aqs status number means
.TP
webp\-completions(1)
Print a shell completion script
.TP
webp\-man(1)
Print a man page in roff, for `man \-l \-` or a package\*(Aqs man directory
.TP
webp\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v0.1.0
